Using Sorting - O(n log n) Time O(1) Space
The idea is to sort the array and traverse it to count frequencies, while tracking the minimum frequency and the result element (res) with that frequency. 
Update values during traversal and finally check the last group to return the required element.

------------------------------------

Using Hash Map or Dictionary - O(n) Time O(n) Space
The idea is to use a map to count the frequency of each element in a single traversal of the array. 
Then, iterate over the map to find the element with the minimum frequency. 
While doing so, maintain mn to track the minimum frequency and res to store the largest element among those with that frequency. 
If a smaller frequency is found, update both values; if the same frequency occurs, update the result by taking the maximum element. 
Finally, return the element having minimum frequency, and in case of a tie, the largest among them.
